# Push fixes to GitHub

After fixing a bug or completing a user-requested fix in this project, **commit and push to GitHub without waiting for the user to ask**.

## Repositories

This workspace uses **two separate git repos**:

| Path | Remote |
|------|--------|
| `frontend/` | `https://github.com/Abdovp/frontend.git` |
| `backend/` | `https://github.com/Abdovp/backend.git` |

Push only the repo(s) that were changed.

## Workflow

1. Finish the fix and verify it (lint/build when reasonable).
2. In each changed repo: `git status` → stage relevant files → commit with a clear message focused on **why**.
3. `git push origin main` for each repo.
4. Tell the user which commit(s) were pushed and that they need to **redeploy on Easypanel** (rebuild, not just restart).

## Do not push when

- The user explicitly says not to push yet.
- Changes are exploratory, incomplete, or broken.
- Only `.env`, secrets, or local config would be included — never commit secrets.

## Git author

If commit fails due to missing identity, use env vars (do not change git config):

`GIT_AUTHOR_NAME=Abdovp`, `GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL=Abdovp@users.noreply.github.com` (same for `GIT_COMMITTER_*`).

## Production note

boyashop.store deploys from GitHub. Unpushed local fixes will **not** appear on the live site until pushed and redeployed.
